Motherboard:
            The main board that connects everything together.

CPU:
    The "brain" that does all the thinking and processing.

RAM:
    The short-term memory for active tasks (makes things run fast right now).

GPU:
    The graphics card that handles visuals and gaming.

HDD & SSD:
          Where all your files, games, and the operating system are saved permanently, SSD is just much faster than HDD.
